<h1 class="title">What is up with ACORN UK?</h1>
<p>
This website is meant to be a way to talk about ACORN and its issues in a constructive way. If you want to add something to the site (e.g. adding a link or document to the Sources section, or issuing a correction to something I have that is wrong), please email <code>cullen1087@gmail.com</code>.
</p>

<div id="outline-container-org01b1760" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org01b1760">ACORN UK Issues</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org01b1760">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgcc4255e" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgcc4255e"><span class="todo TODO">TODO</span> Acorn Oxford, Abersywythe, Lancaster are destroyed</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgcc4255e">
<p>
Multiple branches were destroyed by ACORN National, although in slightly different circumstances. The Oxford one the branch wasn't actually destroyed, but all the active members quit, and it was replaced (by a single staff member?) who continued to run a zombie branch (and as far as I know, it still is a zombie branch). The Abersywythe one was deleted overnight for financial reasons. All of the branch social media sites were controlled by National and deleted. I'm not sure what happened in the Lancaster branch, because I haven't come across any statement put out by them.
</p>

<p>
<a href="resources/copy-of-acorn-oxford-demands.pdf">Oxford Demand Letter</a> (I've cut out the signatures from the document).
</p>

<p>
<a href="resources/acorn-aberystwyth.pdf">Acorn Abersywythe statement</a> (same thing is also explained in a)
</p>

<p>
<img src="images/fuzzy picture.jpg" alt="fuzzy picture.jpg" />
<img src="images/translated-from-welsh-article.jpg" alt="translated-from-welsh-article.jpg" />
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org59dab1a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org59dab1a"><span class="todo TODO">TODO</span> Interference in the democratic processes</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org59dab1a">
<p>
The National Conference this year has been suspended. Previous motions to change Acorn's structure were not allowed. Paid staff who are meant to be helping branches instead are used to rig elections, e.g. campaigning secretly against motions such as the Palestine motion or the Open-Border motion.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org6c19f62" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org6c19f62"><span class="todo TODO">TODO</span> Exploiting staffer</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org6c19f62">
<p>
Acorn UK affiliates with Wade Rathke who has track record of union busting. I've heard that junior staff organisers are underpaid and overworked although like all discussion in the union, it is kept hush-hush, and there is no way to substantiate any allegations. Is this a systemic issue?
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org70d2f31" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org70d2f31"><span class="todo TODO">TODO</span> No discussion, self-reflection or even communication between different branches is allowed?</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org70d2f31">
<p>
I don't get why the members who left Acorn in my branch left so quietly, same applies for Acorn Oxford. I feel like I'm taking crazy pills talking to members in Acorn today who want to keep all the issues we're facing as an organisation secret. How will most members even know there is a problem if we don't ever acknowledge it?
</p>

<p>
Bafflingly one of the demands of the Oxford is to talk
</p>

<p>
I feel like I understand just tip of the iceberg when it comes to understanding what's going on and why. As I find out more, I will add to this site.
</p>

<p>
Some of the discussions that have resulted in member repression is around Refugee and declaring solidarity with Palestine.
</p>

<p>
Issue is not <i>necessarily</i> with some of the strategic decisions that National have taken - I understand the arguments as to why taking explicitly communist policies (having official positions in-solidarity with immigrants, Palestine solidarity) - it is more that the . It is like there is a suspicion of the membership itself, like every single conversation is happening in
</p>

<p>
The branch
</p>
</div>
